NBA FINALS: MAVERICKS v HEAT
June 4, 2011
Joel Anthony
START_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT
 
 
  
 
  
  
   
  Q. Before this game ended, you did a lot of good things.   
 JOEL ANTHONY: Yes, we definitely felt unhappy about closing out that way, isn't characteristic of this team, how we've been playing. We did enough good things. We feel confident that we can rectify our mistakes and come back tomorrow and play a stronger game.   
  
  Q. The way you closed Game 2, is that a momentum swing at all?   
 JOEL ANTHONY: No. We'll see when tomorrow comes. But we feel confident in terms of being able to win here on the road. If anything, we're more hungry because of how we let that one game slip away.   
  
  Q. Does the fact that you guys have dealt with adversity several times give you the confidence you can deal with this?   
 JOEL ANTHONY: Definitely. This team has been in tough situations. We've gone through it throughout this, and we're going to continue to go back to the drawing board and fix our mistakes and come back even stronger.   
  
  Q. Obviously rebounds was a huge thing in Game 1 and even in Game 2. What's the key to getting the rebounds --  
 JOEL ANTHONY: It has to be a greater focus in terms of (Indiscernible). We have to make sure we do a better job of finding bodies. The combination of both us being aggressive and making sure we get offensive rebounds.   
   
    
  
  

END_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT